The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, Aug. 22: The empowered committee on value-added tax (VAT) will hold a two-day meeting beginning tomorrow to discuss issues related to the implementation of the new tax system, including the uniform floor rate (UFR) for bullion items. The officials, mainly tax commissioners, will meet tomorrow followed by state finance ministers the next day. Besides the UFR, tax rates on processed food items, introduction of an 8 per cent tax rate and reluctance of eight states to introduce the VAT are expected to come up for discussion.

 New Delhi, Aug. 22: The Oriental Bank of Commerce (OBC), along with the Bank of Baroda and Bank of Maharashtra, will form a joint venture in Malaysia. They are awaiting the Reserve Bank?s approval for this.

 Mumbai, Aug. 22: Radico Khaitan today said it will set up a wholly owned subsidiary abroad for promoting international business, including the export of Radico?s products all over the world. 

 Mumbai, Aug. 22: The Securities and Exchange Board of India (Sebi) has asked Magadh Stock Exchange Association in Bihar, which is already acting as an unrecognised bourse, not to assist, regulate or control the dealings in securities until further directions.

 Mumbai, Aug. 22: Dr Reddy?s Laboratories has received a tentative approval from the United States Food and Drug Administration for its diabetes drug, Glimepiride.

 New Delhi, Aug. 22: Maruti Udyog Ltd today sounded a note of caution over growth prospects in the near term due to the rising oil prices, exchange rate fluctuations and commodity price trends.

 New Delhi, Aug. 22: Metro Tyres today said it has bid for acquiring Falcon Tyres. However, the company is ?open to independent alternate production arrangement? in case it fails to wrest Falcon, which is also being eyed by other big players.




